-install python 3.0 or latter

In Terminal:

mkdir soen344
cd soen344
python3 -m venv venv
. venv/bin/activate
pip install flask

put the following code in hello.py in soen344 folder
from flask import Flask
app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route(‘/’)
def hello_world():
   return ‘Hello, World!’

//the below line is to install a server for running the flask app
pip install gunicorn

//run the app
gunicorn -w 4 hello:app

//mysql support
pip install mysqlclient

//Azure database connection string
Soen344room3
"mysql://eglen@eglencecaj:Soen344room3@eglencecaj.mysql.database.azure.com/soen344"

..........................................Steps.........................................
DB commands when schema changes:

python migrate.py db init
python migrate.py db migrate
python migrate.py db upgrade